# LiVEiT® Commercial Licensing

The LiVEiT® Framework is released as an open-source project to encourage collaboration, learning and innovation.

While the framework source code may be used under the terms of its applicable open-source licence, the **LiVEiT®** name, logos and official branding remain protected intellectual property.

This document explains how commercial use of the LiVEiT® brand is managed.

---

# Open Source and Commercial Use

The LiVEiT® Framework has been designed to encourage adoption by developers, organisations and educators.

You are welcome to:

* Study the framework.
* Modify the framework.
* Build projects using the framework.
* Contribute improvements.
* Develop commercial software based upon the framework, where permitted by the applicable software licence.

Commercial use of the source code does not automatically grant the right to use the LiVEiT® trademark or official branding.

---

# The LiVEiT® Brand

The following remain protected:

* LiVEiT®
* Official logos
* Official wordmarks
* Brand identity
* Visual assets
* Brand documentation

These assets may only be used in accordance with this Branding Guide and applicable trademark law.

---

# Commercial Branding

If your commercial product uses the LiVEiT® Framework, you should clearly distinguish between:

* Your organisation or product.
* The underlying LiVEiT® Framework.

The LiVEiT® brand should not become the primary identity of a third party commercial product without permission.

---

# Official Partnerships

Authorised commercial partners may be granted permission to use official LiVEiT® branding under a separate written agreement.

Such permission may include:

* Display of official logos.
* Approved marketing material.
* Certified partnership statements.
* Product compatibility branding.

Any such permissions will define the scope and conditions of use.

---

# Third Party Products

Developers may create applications, websites or services that integrate with the LiVEiT® Framework.

Where appropriate, these products may describe themselves using statements such as:

* "powered by LiVEiT®."
* "inspired by LiVEiT®."
* "Built using the LiVEiT® Framework."
* "Compatible with the LiVEiT® Framework."

These statements must be truthful and must not imply endorsement, certification or ownership unless permission has been granted.

---

# Prohibited Commercial Use

You must not:

* Sell products that present themselves as official LiVEiT® products without authorisation.
* Use official branding in a misleading manner.
* Modify the LiVEiT® logo and continue to represent it as an official mark.
* Register confusingly similar trademarks, logos or domain names.
* Suggest endorsement or partnership where none exists.

These restrictions protect both the LiVEiT® brand and those who rely upon it.

---

# Licensing Enquiries

If your organisation wishes to:

* Use official LiVEiT® branding.
* Become an authorised commercial partner.
* Incorporate official branding into commercial products.
* Discuss licensing opportunities.

Please contact the LiVEiT® project through the official communication channels.

---

# Fair Use

Reasonable descriptive use of the LiVEiT® name is generally acceptable when accurately referring to the framework.

Examples include:

* Documentation.
* Tutorials.
* Reviews.
* Educational material.
* Compatibility statements.

Such references should always be factual and should not imply official approval.

---

# Future Licensing

As the LiVEiT® ecosystem continues to grow, additional commercial licensing programmes or partnership opportunities may be introduced.

Any future programmes will be published through the official LiVEiT® documentation and repository.

---

# Summary

The LiVEiT® Framework is intended to encourage innovation through open source collaboration while protecting the integrity of the LiVEiT® brand.

Developers are encouraged to build with the framework, contribute to its development and create new ideas, while respecting the registered trademark, official branding and associated intellectual property.
